The paper proposes a method for prototype-based fuzzy clustering using transfer learning. This involves leveraging knowledge from a related domain to improve clustering in the target domain. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), social and information networks (cs.SI), and data mining (cs.DM). The paper's focus on clustering and transfer learning makes cs.LG and cs.AI the most likely categories, followed by cs.CV due to the potential applications in image and video analysis. The use of knowledge from related domains also suggests relevance to cs.SI, while the use of objective functions for clustering aligns with cs.DM.
